## 🚀 Usage Examples

### Python API - Offline Execution

```python
from offline_bridge import OfflineRuntime, ExecutionMode

# Create runtime (auto mode - detects network)
runtime = OfflineRuntime(mode=ExecutionMode.AUTO)

# Execute Python offline
result = runtime.execute('python', '''
print("Hello from offline Python!")
for i in range(5):
    print(f"Count: {i}")
''')

print(result['stdout'])
```

### Force Offline Mode

```python
# Force offline execution
runtime = OfflineRuntime(mode=ExecutionMode.OFFLINE)

# All executions use local interpreters
result = runtime.execute('python', code)
result = runtime.execute('javascript', js_code)
result = runtime.execute('rust', rust_code)
# All run completely offline!
```

### Force Online Mode

```python
# Use cloud resources when available
runtime = OfflineRuntime(mode=ExecutionMode.ONLINE)

# Will use cloud acceleration or fallback to offline
result = runtime.execute('python', code)
```

### Auto Mode (Recommended)

```python
# Automatically choose best option
runtime = OfflineRuntime(mode=ExecutionMode.AUTO)

# Uses online if available, offline if not
result = runtime.execute('python', code)
# No code changes needed!
```

---

## 🧪 Execute Multiple Languages

### Offline Execution Examples

```python
from offline_bridge import OfflineRuntime, ExecutionMode

runtime = OfflineRuntime(mode=ExecutionMode.OFFLINE)

# Python
python_result = runtime.execute('python', 'print("Hello Python")')

# JavaScript  
js_result = runtime.execute('javascript', 'console.log("Hello JS")')

# Ruby
ruby_result = runtime.execute('ruby', 'puts "Hello Ruby"')

# PHP
php_result = runtime.execute('php', 'echo "Hello PHP";')

# Go
go_result = runtime.execute('go', 'package main\nfunc main() { println("Hello Go") }')

# Rust
rust_result = runtime.execute('rust', 'fn main() { println!("Hello Rust"); }')

# ALL WORK OFFLINE!
```

---

## 📦 Caching System

### Automatic Result Caching

```python
runtime = OfflineRuntime()

# First execution - runs code
result1 = runtime.execute('python', 'print("Hello")')
# Execution time: 50ms

# Second execution - uses cache
result2 = runtime.execute('python', 'print("Hello")')  
# Execution time: <1ms (cached!)
```

### Package Caching

```python
from offline_bridge import OfflineRuntime

runtime = OfflineRuntime()

# Cache Python package for offline use
import requests  # Download once
runtime.cache_package('requests', requests)

# Now available offline forever!
```

---

## 🔧 Angeh Lang Integration

### Offline Runtime Module

```scheme
;; Load offline runtime
(import offline-runtime)

;; Create runtime
(def runtime (offline-runtime-new))

;; Register all engines
(register-all-offline-engines! runtime)

;; Execute Python offline
(def result (execute-code-offline runtime 'python "print('Hello')"))

;; Execute JavaScript offline
(def js-result (execute-code-offline runtime 'javascript "console.log('Hi')"))

;; Universal execution (auto mode)
(def auto-result (execute-universal runtime 'python code))
```

---

## 🌍 Network Detection

### Automatic Detection

```python
runtime = OfflineRuntime(mode=ExecutionMode.AUTO)

print(f"Network available: {runtime.network_available}")
print(f"Internet available: {runtime.internet_available}")

# Runtime automatically adjusts execution strategy
```

### Manual Override

```python
runtime = OfflineRuntime()

# Force offline
runtime.set_mode(ExecutionMode.OFFLINE)

# Force online
runtime.set_mode(ExecutionMode.ONLINE)

# Auto detect
runtime.set_mode(ExecutionMode.AUTO)
```

---

## 💾 Local Cache Management

### Cache Location

```
Default: ~/.angeh_cache/
├── execution_cache.pkl    # Cached execution results
├── packages/              # Cached packages
├── models/               # Cached AI models
└── languages/            # Language runtimes
```

### Cache Operations

```python
runtime = OfflineRuntime(cache_dir="/custom/cache/path")

# Manual cache operations
runtime._save_cache()  # Save to disk
runtime._load_cache()  # Load from disk
```

---

## 🚀 Performance Comparison

| Mode | First Run | Subsequent Runs | Network Required |
|------|-----------|-----------------|------------------|
| Offline | ~50ms | ~50ms | ❌ No |
| Online | ~200ms | ~150ms | ✅ Yes |
| Auto + Network | ~200ms | ~1ms (cached) | ➖ Optional |
| Auto + No Network | ~50ms | ~1ms (cached) | ❌ No |

